The Perfect Poem

I have been searching,
In agony, for the perfect poem.
A poem that says it all ‚Äî 
All my sorrows, all my joys.
The words that paint the picture
None but my heart can see.
A poem that lives, that reaches,
Beyond what I can.

But I never seem to see,
The destination of my journey.
Always out of reach, always out of touch.
I extend my hand,
Only to catch empty feathers. 
The words I cast, the paint that drops,
Everything falls into the wrong spot.

But can you see,
My toilsome search, 
For that of which I may never uncover. 
An undying want,
To rip open my heart for the world to see.
Yet what would it see?
My tears, my laughter? 
The words time has taken away ‚Äî
Or what it has failed to steal?

Perhaps this journey,
This endless, beautiful journey,
Is my poem.
My struggles the words, my love the paint,
Perfection woven only in imperfection.
My tainted life, my perfect poem.

A Snail‚Äôs Path ‚Äî What is Success?

The vine is higher than the sky,
The leaves are too vast for my eye.
Inching steadily with each step I take,
My shell exacerbating my body‚Äôs ache.

If I let go, the pain would stop,
But if I capitulate, I won‚Äôt see the top.
Never to quench the dew on the leaves,
Never to glimpse what I may achieve. 

And so, I keep going,
Gradually, I keep climbing.
One branch at a time,
Leaving behind my slime. 

Maybe, one day I‚Äôll finally make it,
Because no matter what, I won‚Äôt quit.
Perhaps I‚Äôll never reach the top,
But that doesn‚Äôt mean I‚Äôll ever stop.

As long as the sun keeps shining,
I know that I will keep trying.
Even if the world thinks I‚Äôve failed,
If I persevere I‚Äôll have success nailed. 

As the sole secret to success is to try,
To give it your all and never ask why.
For at the end if you never recede,
You will most surely learn to succeed.
